description:
Rena Mero is an ex-wrestler, ex-model, part-time actess who has quit the entertainment industry in latter years to spend time with her family.

In the comic-book industry, she was the artistic inspiration for the first "generation" of the character The 10th Muse and her alter-ego Emma Sonnett while the title was with TidalWave Studios at Image Comics. (TidalWave Studios later became indy publisher Alias Enterprises then BlueWater Comics.)
name: Rena Mero

description:
Alley Baggett is a Playboy Magazine centerfold who branched out into acting and glamour modelling as well as internet marketing of her image as a sex goddess.

Alley Cat, an Image Comics character, was based on her.

The main comic run of Alley Cat had 6 issues (plus a Prelude and Preview) as well as an accompanying "Lingerie Special". Later, a 1-shot crossover with Lady Pendragon was released. Most of these books had photo covers featuring Alley Baggett as Alley Baggett/Alley Cat.
name: Alley Baggett

deck: Delando "Lando" Nino is a Filipino comics artist.
description: Delando "Lando" Nino is a Filipino comics artist who worked for Warren Publishing in the 1970s and 1980s. He is the brother of comic artist Alex Nino and together they sometimes published as "The Nino Brothers".
name: Delando Nino
